# Supabase Edge Functions

## Runtime & Conventions

- **Runtime**: Deno (TypeScript). Use `Deno.serve()` entry point.
- **Imports**: Use `esm.sh` or `jsr:` imports. No npm.
- **Validation**: Zod schemas from `packages/shared-types/` (import via URL or vendored).
- **CORS**: Use shared CORS handler from `_shared/cors.ts`.
- **Auth**: Extract JWT from `Authorization` header. Use `supabase.auth.getUser(token)` to verify.
- **Secrets**: Read from `Deno.env.get('SECRET_NAME')`. Never hardcode API keys.

## Error Handling

Return RFC 7807 Problem Details for all errors:

```typescript
return new Response(JSON.stringify({
  type: 'https://api.snacky.app/errors/vision-model-failure',
  title: 'Vision Model Failure',
  status: 502,
  detail: 'All vision model providers failed. Please try again.',
}), { status: 502, headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' } });
```

## AI Model Fallback Pattern

Vision pipeline uses triple-provider fallback:

```typescript
const providers = [
  { name: 'gpt-5.4', fn: callOpenAI, timeout: 10_000 },
  { name: 'gemini-3.1-pro', fn: callGemini, timeout: 10_000 },
  { name: 'claude-sonnet-4.6', fn: callAnthropic, timeout: 10_000 },
];

for (const provider of providers) {
  try {
    return await withTimeout(provider.fn(imageBase64, prompt), provider.timeout);
  } catch (err) {
    log.warn(`${provider.name} failed, trying next`, { error: err });
  }
}
return errorResponse(502, 'All providers failed');
```

## Structured Logging

Use structured JSON logs. Fields: `timestamp`, `level`, `function_name`, `trace_id`, `user_id` (hashed), `message`, `metadata`. Never log raw PII.

